# S2-7: Production Deployment & CI Integration

This task focuses on setting up the production infrastructure and ensuring every Pull Request generates a "Deploy Preview" for easy review.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I am proposing **Render** (render.com) as the primary deployment platform because it supports monorepo structures, managed PostgreSQL, and automatic "Preview Environments" for GitHub Pull Requests out of the box.

## Proposed Changes

### Infrastructure (Render)

#### [NEW] [render.yaml](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20(Python)/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/render.yaml)
Create a Blueprint file defining:
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (managed).
- **Web Service (Backend)**: Express API running in the `/server` directory.
- **Static Site (Frontend)**: Vite build from the `/client` directory.

### CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

#### [MODIFY] [.github/workflows/ci.yml](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20(Python)/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/.github/workflows/ci.yml)
- Ensure tests run against a clean environment on every push.
- (Manual Step) Enable Render's PR Preview functionality in the Render dashboard once the Blueprint is synced.

### Environment Management

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20(Python)/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/.env.example)
